{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threadInit","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"vtable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since version 2.24, calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" multiple times is allowed,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"but nothing happens except for the first call.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since version 2.32, GLib does not support custom thread implementations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"anymore and the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vtable"},{"text":" parameter is ignored and you should pass ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"type":"text","text":" note"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":" must not be called directly or indirectly in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback from GLib. Also no mutexes may be currently locked","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"while calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"type":"text","text":" note"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" in your program, you have to link with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":